The paper discusses a novel memory-augmented neural network (MANN) that improves the memory ability of neural networks for sequential processing tasks. This topic is closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are covered by the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. The paper also introduces a new RNN cell for refined integration of memory information, which falls under the cs.NE sub-category. Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed model on various experiments, which could be categorized under cs.CL and cs.CV sub-categories.
